<HEADLINE> Sorensen Wins Italy Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Danish rider Rolf Sorensen won the
victory in the prologue to the Tirren-Adriatico cycling race in
Sorrento, Italy, on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Sorensen, who rides for the Rabobank team, beat Dutchman Erik
Dekker and Italian Maurizio Fondriest in the 4-kilometer time
trial, the start of the seven-stage race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
