<HEADLINE> Kazakova, Dmitriev in Russian Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Former Olympic champion Artur
Dmitriev and his partner Oksana Kazakova were selected Wednesday
for the Russian figure skating team to compete at April's world
championships.
</P>
<P>
The pair, who were not picked for the European championships in
January, finished second in the Champions Series final in
Hamilton, Canada, two weeks ago, ahead of third-placed compatriots
Marina Eltsova and Andrei Bushkov.
</P>
<P>
Eltsova and Bushkov are also selected for the Russian team
along with Elena Berezhnaia and Anton Sikharulidze, who were third
at the European championships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
