<HEADLINE> Bonn Trains Soldiers, Offers Military Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Germany is currently training more
than 30 Albanian soldiers and has provided Tirana with jet fighter
engines and military vehicles, according to a senior government
official today.
</P>
<P>
Bonn has supplied 20 engines for MIG jets and 29 military
transport trucks to Albania over the past seven years, Klaus Rose,
a state secretary at the German Defense Ministry, told parliament.
</P>
