<HEADLINE> Shooting Breaks Out in C. Johannesburg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Volleys of automatic
gunfire broke out at Johannesburg's library gardens this
afternoon during a Zulu commemoration of the 1994 Shell House
massacre.
</P>
<P>
Police and Zulu marchers opened fire on one another at about
2:15 p.m. after a single shot fired from the crowd, witnesses
said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of marchers dived for cover when the shooting
started, they said.
</P>
<P>
The shooting lasted about five or six minutes before the
gathering broke up in disarray, said one of the witnesses.
</P>
<P>
So far, reports about casualties are not immediately
available.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 people were killed and over 170 injured in
clashes between Zulu nationalists, the police and African
National Congress supporters in Johannesburg and East Rand
townships on March 28, 1994.
</P>
<P>
Mourners decided to stage the march and service in the library
gardens today because March 28 falls on Good Friday this year.
</P>
<P>
About 20,000 Zulu people were expected to have participated in
the march today to commemorate the bloody day and to call for the
day to be a public holiday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
