<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Historic HK Duathlon Race to Take Express Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A historic sporting event named
Timex Hong Kong International Duathlon Race is to be staged on
April 20, the Hong Kong Triathlon Association (HKTA) and Timex
jointly announced here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The event is to inaugurate the North Lantau Expressway, which
is one of the key projects of the New Airport Core Program and is
scheduled to be open to traffic in May.
</P>
<P>
The landmark running-cycling event takes the expressway which
runs along the northern coast of Lantau Island and to the New
Airport at Chek Lap Kok, which is now under construction. It is
expected to attract more than 600 local and international
athletes, the organizers said.
</P>
<P>
Three different courses have been designated to challenge
competitors of all ages: Course A is a six kilometers run, 40
kilometers cycle race and six more kilometers run; Course B is a 3
kilometers run, 20 kilometers cycle and 3 kilometers run; and
Course C consists of a 3 kilometers run, 20 kilometers cycle and
200 meters run.
</P>
<P>
Bernie Ryan, president of the HKTA, said the Timex Duathlon
will arouse tremendous interest among people of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"In Hong Kong, a city with only 8,000 dedicated cyclists and
30,000 active runners, the potential for 40,000 duathletes is
already in place," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is also a great opportunity for people to participate in
the opening of an expressway which will soon become one of the
city's busiest integral connectors," the HKTA chief continued.
</P>
<P>
"To run along a closed road is a rare experience for
triathletes or duathletes," he added.
</P>
<P>
The race has been sanctioned by the Asian Triathlon
Confederation and the Chinese Triathlon Association has promised
to send a six-member team including five athletes to the event.
</P>
<P>
Athletes are to enter in the individual men's and women's
categories, which include Open, Veteran and Junior groups.
</P>
<P>
And to ensure the safety of athletes, the race will be closed
to spectators. But each competitor could register two guests at
the organizers' discretion.
</P>
<P>
"Generally speaking, the course is flat and not difficult to
the participants. But as it faces the sea, some sectors might be
a bit windy," said Ruth Hunt, director of the race and a former
triathlete herself.
</P>
<P>
The organizers had overcome a lot of difficulties and won over
helping hands from many organizations and departments, she
said. "Some 100 policemen are to be designated in place along the
course to ensure safety and order," she said.
</P>
<P>
"Things have now been put on the right track and everyone
wishes the event to be a success," she added.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has been staging duathlon races ever since 1992. An
international-standard triathlon race includes 1.5 kilometers
swimming, 40 kilometers cycling and 10 kilometers run. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
