<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Privatize Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Zambia announced today it will
privatize other mines such as collieries and gemstone in addition
to copper mines.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency ZANA quoted Minister of Mines and
Mineral Development Christone Tembo as saying in Canada that the
investment climate in his country is still competitive even after
the arrivals of some investors because most of Zambia remains
unexplored.
</P>
<P>
He called on more investors to put money in the mining sector
of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Tembo also told delegates to the Prospectors and Developers
Association of Canada Convention that the Zambian government will
further improve the investment climate in the country.
</P>
<P>
The mines and assets of the state-owned Zambia Consolidated
Copper Mines (ZCCM) have already been offered for sale and 15
foreign companies have submitted a total 26 bids for them.
</P>
</TEXT>
