<HEADLINE> British Prime Minister Calls for Abattoir Hygiene Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- British Prime Minister John Major
has ordered a full report from the Ministry of Agriculture over
hygiene in Britain's abattoirs here today.
</P>
<P>
Major asked the ministry to have a chronology prepared of how
the issue was handled.
</P>
<P>
A Downing Street spokesman said he asked the ministry to
provide him with "one comprehensive document." Once the report is
prepared, it will be made public and statement will be made to the
House of Commons.
</P>
<P>
Major also ordered a report Tuesday from the ministry on what
steps it had taken to deal with the problems and when they had
been implemented. The report will be published soon.
</P>
<P>
Major is already under fire from the main opposition Labor
Party, which last week accused him of covering up a report on
abattoir standards.
</P>
<P>
The party has vowed to create a Food Standard Agency
independent of the Ministry of Agriculture to ensure consumer
interests are not sacrificed to those of farmers. 
