<HEADLINE> China Reaffirms Support for Middle East Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- China is happy about the
significant progress in the Middle East peace process but is
concerned about incidents like Israel's latest decision to build
new Jewish settlements in East Jerusalem, a senior Chinese
diplomat said here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 53rd session of the United Nations Commission
on Human Rights, Alternate Representative of the Chinese
delegation Li Baodong said China has always favored peaceful
negotiations by all parties concerned on the basis of relevant
resolutions of the U.N.
</P>
<P>
He called on the parties concerned to act with prudence,
cherish the peace already achieved and strictly abide by the
concluded agreements.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Commission on Human Rights has provided great support
to the just cause of the Arabs and Palestinians in the occupied
Arab territories over the past years, Li recalled.
</P>
<P>
He suggested the commission help find a solution to serious
human rights violations caused by colonialism, racism, foreign
aggression, occupation and alien rule, and safeguard the
sovereignty and national independence of states.
</P>
<P>
China will continue making contributions to the comprehensive
restoration of the legitimate national rights of the Palestinian
people and to the realization of a lasting peace in the Middle
East, Li said.
</P>
<P>
The current session of the U.N. Commission on Human Rights
started on Monday and will end on April 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
