<HEADLINE> Anti-FN Protest Organizers Complain of Police Violence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The organizers of a protest against
the extreme-right National Front (FN) Tuesday night in Marseille
have complained about the "violent savageness" with which police
stopped their initiative.
</P>
<P>
Several anti-racist and human rights groups condemned in a
communique issued today "this unjustifiable and unqualified
attitude" of police and said that the demonstrators wanted to
protest in a "calm but determined way."
</P>
<P>
They said that police dispersed demonstrators with gear gas
without pre-warning when some 8,000 people protested outside a
meeting hall where FN President Jean-Marie Le Pen and the number
two of the FN Bruno Megret were making speeches.
</P>
