The groups which joined the protest included the Movement
against Racism and for Friendship among Peoples, the League of
Human Rights, SOS Racism and Alarm Citizens.
</P>
<P>
But Marseille police commissioner Michel Sappin said, "All the
interventions of forces of order were carried out in a situation
of defense or repelling acts of violence, degradations or
voluntary arson committed by certain hooded demonstrators."
</P>
<P>
He said that four policemen and one photographer were wounded
in the clash between demonstrators and police, and 12 people were
detained by police. 
