agreements with Portugal on rehabilitation of its main roads
damaged during the civil war, Minister of Public Works Castro
Van-Dunem said in Lisbon.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Portuguese magazine "Trade" during
his recent visit to the west European country published today,
Van-Dunem said four-fifths of Angola's 15,000 kilometers of roads
remain pot-holed and impassable due to the war.
</P>
