<HEADLINE> UK Industrial Output Holds Steady in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Britain's total industrial output
was unchanged in January, and was up 2.4 percent compared with the
same month last year, according to figures released today by the
Office for National Statistics (ONS).
</P>
<P>
Analysts had forecast a 0.2 percent monthly increase and a 2.8
percent annual rise.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing output rose 0.3 percent in January to give a 1.6
percent year-on-year rise, roughly in line with expectations, the
ONS said.
</P>
<P>
It was up 0.3 percent in the three months to January compared
with the previous three months, and was 1.1 percent higher than
the same period a year ago.
</P>
<P>
The British government welcomed the figures, with the Treasury
saying that this showed manufacturing industry continued to enjoy
expansion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
