between the two parties concluded two weeks earlier, the
commission asked the EU Minister Council to approve its proposal
"as soon as possible."
</P>
<P>
Under the initial agreement, the trade benefits of Lome will
not apply to South Africa. Trade relations will be governed by a
separate bilateral agreement, which will contain provisions for
the gradual establishment of a Free Trade Area.
</P>
<P>
In economic terms, South Africa's main benefit from membership
of the convention is that it will be eligible to tender for
European Development Fund projects in all Africa, Caribbean and
Pacific (ACP) countries.
</P>
<P>
At a political level, South Africa's membership of the
convention and its full participation in all Lome institutions
should have important positive effects.
</P>
<P>
"It will undoubtedly increase the political weight of the ACP
group of countries, and influence the political dialogue between
the ACP and the EU on many issues, including the post Lome
debate," the commission said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
According to the commission, it was further agreed, following a
South African proposal, that projects and activities in South
Africa will not be funded from Lome resources -- with the
exception of refugee assistance, if necessary.
</P>
<P>
The commission said South Africa confirmed its preference to
receive continued financial assistance through the European
Program for Reconstruction and Development, which is funded
directly from the EU Community budget.
</P>
<P>
It was hoped that the ACP/EC Joint Council of 24 April will
formally approve the protocol, which would then enter into force
later this year, together with the rest of the revised Lome IV
Convention.
</P>
<P>
The Lome Convention is first signed in 1975 by the then
nine-member European Economic Community and 46 ACP countries with
the aim of boosting trade and economic relations between the EEC
and the ACP group.
</P>
<P>
The Lome IV Convention, which was renewed in 1989 and came into
force in March 1990, has a validity time of 10 years. It has at
present 85 members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
