<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN General Assembly Pays Homage to Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The U.N. General Assembly,
at its first plenary meeting held since January, paid tribute to
the memory of the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Opening the memorial ceremony, General Assembly President
Ismail Razali of Malaysia said that the passing away of Deng
Xiaoping is "a loss not only to China, but to the international
community as well."
</P>
<P>
"With his vision of reform and pragmatism," he said, "Mr. Deng
will be remembered as an astute leader who helped steer the cause
of China towards international peace and security during a time of
global transition."
</P>
<P>
"He will be also be remembered for his unparalleled
contributions as the chief of architect of modernization,
liberalization and economic prosperity in China," he said.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the General Assembly, he requested the permanent
representative of China to convey "our heartfelt condolences and
profound sympathy to the government and people of China and to the
bereaved family."
</P>
<P>
Under the invitation of Ismail, the member states then stood up
and observed a minute of silence in tribute to Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Representative of Africa, Asia, Eastern Europe, Latin American
and Europe then addressed the General Assembly, expressing their
"profound sorrow" on the passing of the Deng Xiaoping. The
representative of the United States, Bill Richardson, also spoke on
the behalf of the host country.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Permanent Representative to the United Nations Qin
Huasun told the General Assembly that Deng Xiaoping was an
outstanding leader enjoying high prestige acknowledged by the
Chinese people of all ethnic groups, the chief architect of
China's reform, opening-up and modernization and founder of the
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
He said Deng led China in re-determining an international
strategy, adhering to an independent foreign policy of peace,
safeguarding world peace, promoting world development and opposing
hegemonism and power politics.
</P>
<P>
These efforts, he said, have opened up "a new situation of
China's relations with foreign countries in a new era" and made
"historical contributions" to developing and strengthening China's
friendly relations with all countries in the world on the basis of
the Five Principles of Peaceful Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
With regards to the future, Ambassador Qin said the central
collective leadership with President Jiang Zemin at the core will
lead the Chinese people in carrying forward the behest of Deng
Xiaoping, building China into a prosperous, democratic and
civilized socialist country and developing friendly relations of
cooperation with all countries in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
