<HEADLINE> Neem Tree Nurseries to Be Built in Tanga, Eastern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Tanga-based
Association for Rural Development Promotion (ARDP) is planning
to set up neem tree nurseries in Tanga, eastern Tanzania, in a bid
to raise the tree products which are full of therapeutic values.
</P>
<P>
ARDP Secretary Fredolin Mbunda told reporters here today that
medical materials drawn from the tree can cure 124 human and
several animal diseases.
</P>
<P>
The promotion of the neem tree, popularly known as muarobaini,
would enable rural residents to have access to the tree products
and thus ease the shortage of drugs in rural areas in the region,
he said.
</P>
<P>
More than 500,000 neem trees have been planted in the region.
</P>
<P>
The ARDP is planning to raise 2,000 individuals, groups,
schools and the municipal authorities to help further plant the
tree in the region.
</P>
<P>
The ARDP has put forward an application and sent a request to
the ministries of Health and Agriculture for permission to
establish a backyard pharmacy.
</P>
<P>
The secretary appealed to donors, environmentalists and
researchers to support the association in the promotion of the
tree, which has been used for years in India for making human and
animal medicines.
</P>
<P>
The association was formed in 1994 to help alleviate poverty
and deprivation among the rural population in the Tanga region.
