<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0083 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Expounds Stand on Right to Self-determination </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Alternate representative of the
Chinese delegation Liu Xinsheng said here today that a correct
understanding and application of the principle of
self-determination is of particular importance despite the
profound changes in the international situation in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the 53rd session of the United Nations Commission
on Human Rights, Liu said: "The history of international relations
since World War II demonstrates that when a nation has yet to win
independence and liberation, when a sovereign state is subjected
to alien aggression and occupation, and as a result, the people's
right to self-determination is illegally deprived of, there is no
respect for human rights and freedom to speak of, still less the
country's economic prosperity and social development."
</P>
<P>
"The recognition of the right to self-determination means
respect for a state's sovereignty, independence and territorial
integrity, so that people can totally liberate themselves from
foreign aggression and subjugation and choose their own political
and economic systems and development paths according to their
particular national circumstances. No country should impose its
own ideology, social system and development model on others," He
said.
</P>
<P>
Liu noted, "The domineering over the weak by the strong and the
bullying of the small by the big on various pretexts constitute
gross violations of the Charter of the United Nations and of the
principle of self-determination. And so does interference with
others' affairs by exerting political pressure, imposing economic
sanctions or even resorting to force. Such violations should
naturally be condemned by the international community."
</P>
<P>
However, "it is entirely a country's internal affair to employ
political, legal, economic and administrative measures to deal
with problems concerning ethnic groups through adjusting their
relations", he stressed. "Inappropriate application of the
principle of self-determination to the internal affairs of
multi-national countries apparently exceeds the definition and
scope of the right, as set forth in the above-mentioned
international human rights instruments."
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, the principle of self-determination should not be
regarded as the basis to address and resolve problems with respect
to ethnic groups in a country, still less should it be used as an
excuse by foreign forces to support or encourage the impairment of
a state's territorial integrity, sovereignty and independence." he
added.
</P>
<P>
Liu concluded, "The restoration of the Palestinian people's
rights, including the right to self-determination, and an early,
just and reasonable solution to the question of Palestine are key
to the realization of peace and stability in the Middle East
region. We hope that the parties concerned, guided by the
principle of "land for peace", and based on the relevant
resolutions of the U.N., strive for a comprehensive, just and
lasting settlement to the Middle East question through political
negotiations."
</P>
<P>
The current session meets here from March 10 to April 18. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
