<HEADLINE> Hawaiian Chinese Community Entertains Chinese Sailors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONOLULU, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Local Chinese community gave a
dinner party here today to entertain some 100 Chinese sailors
before their departure after a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The sailors were from a Chinese naval delegation consisting of
three naval vessels and some 800 sailors. The Chinese warships
arrived in Pear Harbor on Sunday and will leave for San Diego, a
southern Californian port, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The visit of the naval delegation has brought local Chinese
community together, said Kennth Chong, president of the Hawaiian
Chinese Chamber of Commerce, at the dinner.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese community has been trying to keep
their traditional cultural heritage, which was strengthened by
this visit.
</P>
<P>
The visit has also helped promote friendship between China and
the United States, Chong said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of local Chinese Americans have visited the Chinese
warships over the past two days. And Chinese sailors have toured
many places including Chinatown, some historical sites and Hawaii
University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
