<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Quake Shakes Central Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A moderate earthquake with an
estimated magnitude of 3.7 on the Richter scale shook the central
Philippines tonight, the Philippine Institute of Volcanology and
Seismology said.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, the second in two days, hit Mindoro island at
8:12 p.m. and aftershocks were expected, the institution said in a
preliminary report.
</P>
<P>
The institute said it expected no damage caused by the quake
whose epicenter was located under the seabed 23 km northwest of
Puerto Galera islet.
</P>
<P>
The institute said the quake was possibly caused by tectonic
fault.
</P>
<P>
Early Wednesday morning, a strong earthquake measuring 7 on the
Richter scale hit Mindanao in the southern Philippines. But the
quake, whose epicenter was also located under the seabed, caused
no casualties.
</P>
<P>
Usually an earthquake with a magnitude of 4 will be damaging if
it hits a densely populated area.  
</P>
</TEXT>
