<HEADLINE> Nanjing to Stage International Kite Flying Competition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, eastern China, March 13 (Xinhua) -- An international
kite flying competition will be staged in the eastern Chinese city
of Nanjing from April 13-17, organizers said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kite fans from about ten countries and regions, including the
United States, Britain, France, Malaysia and host China, will
compete in the meet.
</P>
<P>
Points will be awarded on the outlooks of the kites, their
flying conditions and the time they stay in the air, organizers
said.
</P>
<P>
China and several Asian countries are known for their wide
variety of traditional kites, which are mostly made of bamboo
skeletons and paper or silk. 
</P>
