<HEADLINE> Ex-Libris Exhibition Staged in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 Ex-Libris Hong Kong
Invitation Exhibition was staged here today at Hong Kong Cultural
Center.
</P>
<P>
On display were more than 800 works of the elegant art, created
 by some 220 artists from China's inland areas, Hong Kong and
Taiwan regions, Japan, Singapore and the Republic of Korea.
</P>
<P>
Among the exhibits, some 90 were based on the theme of Hong
Kong's returning to her motherland on July 1, featuring bauhinia,
which is to be borne on the regional flag and regional emblem of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR), and even the
portrait of Tung Chee Hwa, first chief executive of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
Also presenting their works were children from China's inland
areas, where ex-libris related activities are well promoted among
the young people.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, organized by a local arts association and
sponsored by the Urban Council, runs until next Monday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
