<HEADLINE> Fujian's Party Leader Vows to Boost Ties with Taiwan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Fujian Province will take
substantial measures to develop its relations with Taiwan,
especially in the trade and economic fields.
</P>
<P>
Local Party and government departments have been urged to
familiarize themselves with the work concerning the issue of
Taiwan and the related tasks set for the whole province of Fujian.
</P>
<P>
Xi Jinping, vice-secretary of the Fujian Provincial Committee
of the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the remarks today at a
provincial conference on the issue of Taiwan, which opened in
Fuzhou, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Xi pledged to be firmly united with the CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core and to carry out
the Party's policies, principles and major programs on the issue
of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He said that to make the most of the opportunity to make Fuzhou
and Xiamen cities into pilot ports for experimenting with direct
flights and shipping services across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
This year, Fujian should continue to support the 4,580
Taiwan-funded enterprises in the province, while further improving
the local investment environment and helping Taiwan entrepreneurs
solve their problems, he said.
</P>
<P>
Xi asked that the development of special zones for Taiwanese
investors be accelerated, and that they be made into important
bases for attracting funds from the island province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
