<HEADLINE> Donation Given to Ethiopian Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The African ambassadors'
wives group today donated here skills training material, clothes
and other items for refugees in eastern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The donation which includes sewing machines, accessories and
clothes worth over 6,100 U.S. Dollars, will be sent to women and
children in Aware refugee camps in Jijiga area, eastern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Dean of the group Awa Diop Fall handed over the donation items
to David Lambo, regional liaison representative for Africa of the
U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), and to Ayalew Awoke,
representative of the Administration for Refugee and Returnee
Affairs of the Ethiopian government.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years the group has raised over 40,000 U.S.
Dollars for humanitarian causes and has been able to make
important contributions to the Organization of African Unity
(OAU) peace fund as well as to other welfare activities in
Ethiopia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
