<HEADLINE> Iraq Calls for Release of POWs From Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Iraq today urged today Islamic
world to support the efforts to get freed Iraqi prisoners of war
allegedly detained in Iran for more than 15 years.
</P>
<P>
Iraq News Agency quoted an government information official as
saying that thousands of Iraqi POWs, who were captured during the
eight-year war between the two countries, are still detained in
Iran.
</P>
<P>
The official said in the interview with the agency that Iraq
had freed 39,044 Iranian POWs in August 1990 and Iraq is no longer
detaining any Iranian POWs.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of Iran's Prisoners of War Committee, Abdullah Nejfi
recently accused Iraq of still holding a large number of Iranian
prisoners of war and refusing to release them.
</P>
<P>
The official said that the International Committee of the Red
Cross (ICRC) has affirmed several times, the latest of which was
in a statement issued in Geneva on December 29 last year, that
thousands of Iraqi POW's were still detained in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The POW's problem between Iraq and Iran is the most thorny
issue that has prevented the two countries from normalizing their
relations after ending the war in 1988. 
</P>
</TEXT>
