<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Ahmed Esmat Abdul-Maguid,
secretary-general of the Arab League arrived here today for
celebrations marking the Day of Unity with South Lebanon, which
falls on March 14.
</P>
<P>
At the Beirut International Airport, Abdul-Maguid called for
a unity of the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that the occasion of the South Lebanon's Day
demonstrates the determination of the Lebanese and the Arab nation
to prove that they are "one nation."
</P>
<P>
A series of nation-wide activities are scheduled for today and
Friday to mark the first Israeli aggression of Lebanon on March
14, 1978.
</P>
<P>
On the Arab League's role in seeking a solution of the south
Lebanon's problem, Abdul-Maguid said that the organization is not
"hesitant or reluctant at all to do what it is demanded to do and
what it sees as a duty."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on a recent Israeli decision to build additional
Jewish settlements in Arab East Jerusalem, the Arab League chief
stressed the decision "threatens the peace process" in the region
and constitutes another challenge for the Arab nation.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the Israeli decision was not only
condemned by all the Arab states, but also condemned by most of
the countries in the United Nations and in the U.N. security
council.
</P>
<P>
He confirmed that contacts are currently being held between
Arab leaders in light of the Israeli challenges and these
contacts "could lead to an Arab summit, small-sized or enlarged."
</P>
