The U.N., which is at a crossroads with the changing global
power structure, needs to be revitalized in order to solve
pressing world problems and ensure the future of mankind, he said.
</P>
<P>
Certain developments have undermined the principles of
democracy in the U.N., Gujral said.
</P>
<P>
If the present situation was allowed to continue further, he
warned, the world body would fail to achieve the ideals and goals
for which it had been formed.  
