<HEADLINE> (repeat with a correction in Para Two) Regional Autonomy of National Minorities Areas Lauded (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The State also inclines to the autonomous areas in financial,
taxation, investment, loan-granting, foreign trade,
poverty-alleviation, educational and cultural policies, which has
helped to promote development in the ethnic-minority areas.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the per capita income of farmers in the
autonomous areas reached 1,142 yuan in 1995, with farmers'
per-capita income in 22 counties reaching 2,000 yuan. The average
economic growth rate in the five autonomous regions also exceeded
the national average last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang noted that the system of regional autonomy of minority
nationalities is very instrumental to the fostering of cadres of
minority nationalities.
</P>
<P>
"As for myself, I would not be what I'm like today, if without
the system," said Wang, who had been a cowherd of the Miao ethnic
group till 11, became China's youngest official at the ministry
level when he was 46.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the number of carders of minority
nationalities in China has exceeded 2.48 million.
</P>
<P>
In China, the heads of autonomous areas at all levels are
assumed by people of ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
To cater to the latest developments, China will modify the 1984
law and those formulated earlier in the near future, according to
Wang.
</P>
<P>
"Stepping up legislation will provide an effective guarantee
for the system of regional autonomy of national minorities," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that the Nationalities Committee will
promulgate a law concerning protection of the rights and interests
of people of the national minorities scattered around, a law on
the language and characters of the ethnic groups and regulations
on autonomy in the five autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wang expressed his confidence that a relatively
complete system of socialist legality and supervision for issues
relating to national minorities will be set up before the year
2000. 
