<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Forces Launch New Operation In East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
launched a combined new operation involving the army, navy and
airforce today with the aim to destroy all known Tamil rebels'
camps in the Mullaitivu jungles and along the eastern sea coast of
the country.
</P>
<P>
According to a military press release this evening, gunboats
and fighter aircraft joined in the operation.
</P>
<P>
Air force pilots reported direct hits on the targets while
ground troop learned that the rebels were asking for help from
their leaders as they had suffered heavy casualties.
</P>
<P>
Several camps in the rebel base complex and coastal rebel camps
have been destroyed, the release said.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 14-year war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the island country.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
