<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Indonesia's Banda Aceh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 4.4 on
the Richter scale jolted Banda Aceh and its environs in Eastern
Indonesia for two minutes this morning, according to reports
reaching here from Banda Aceh.
</P>
<P>
The quake's epicenter was 21 km beneath the sea, the local
geophysical and meteorological office said.
</P>
<P>
However, the office did not say the exact time of the quake.
</P>
<P>
There was no immediate report of casualties and material loss
caused by the quake.  
</P>
</TEXT>
