<HEADLINE> 7 Killed, 11 Injured in Israeli-Jordanian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Seven Israeli school-girls
were killed and 11 others injured today in a Jordanian border
area when a Jordanian soldier opened fire at them.
</P>
<P>
The shooting took place in Naharayim in the northern part of
the Israeli-Jordanian border, when dozens of Israeli students
from Beit Shemesh came by buses on school outing.
</P>
<P>
The soldier managed to empty his first magazine of bullets
before being overpowered by his fellow soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Some of the seriously wounded have been taken to a local
Jordanian hospital for treatment, and some others taken back to
Israel.
</P>
<P>
The place where the shooting took place is a scenic island
area on the Jordan River, which had been occupied by Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel returned this area to Jordan under the peace treaty
signed in 1994, but Israelis still have full access to the area
for sightseeing and outing.
</P>
<P>
Today's shooting occurred during a time of rising tension
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian King Hussein and Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu recently exchanged angry letters over the current
Israeli-Palestinian peace deadlock.
</P>
<P>
King Hussein has strongly criticized Israeli government for
endangering the peace process with its hardline policies.
</P>
</TEXT>
