<HEADLINE> IBM Sees Better Opportunities in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The chairman of the US-based IBM
Corporation predicted today that the information technology giant
will play a greater role in China's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting this afternoon with Chinese Vice-Premier Wu
Bangguo at Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the central
government, Louis Gerstner Jr. said that IBM will build its branch
in China into a large-scale company to serve China's modernization
drive, and help China to increase exports and create jobs for the
Chinese in the hi-tech sector worldwide.
</P>
<P>
He said that IBM will use its advanced information technology
to facilitate technological restructuring of state-owned
enterprises in China in a move to improve their competitiveness.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that the cooperation between IBM and China has been
fruitful; the sustained, rapid and healthy growth of China's
economy provides a broad range of cooperative opportunities
between China and IBM.
</P>
<P>
"IBM and China enjoy a sound foundation of cooperation. On this
foundation, we wish to further expand our cooperation, especially
in such areas as building information networks in cities and
upgrading technology of state-owned enterprises," he said.
</P>
<P>
Gerstner will be in China from March 11-14 on a business trip.
</P>
</TEXT>
