<HEADLINE> Meeting On Promoting Peaceful Reunification Of China In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The fifth executive council of
the China Council for the Promotion of Peaceful Reunification was
held today here in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Participants said that they will remember Deng Xiaoping's wish
and strive to reunify the motherland with the principle of
"peaceful reunification, and one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
Qian Weichang, vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference and president of the China Council for the
Promotion of Peaceful Reunification, which was founded in
September of 1988, reported that adherence to the "one China"
principle is fundamental to peaceful reunification and developing
relations across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Although there have been significant achievements in the
campaign to stop separatism and "Taiwan independence", anti-China
forces worldwide are still blocking China's reunification, he
noted.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan authorities are trying to turn the island into an
"independent political entity", while engaging in activities that
create "two Chinas", he said, pointing out that the so-called
"national development council" of the Taiwan authorities recently
further demonstrated its attempt to create a separation and to
hinder the reunification process.
</P>
<P>
Qian said that China's reunification requires efforts of the
people of Taiwan, and that more exchanges should be made with them.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Tinghan, deputy head of the United Front Work Department
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, voiced
the hope that the China Council for the Promotion of Peaceful
Reunification will continue to implement the guidelines of
President Jiang Zemin's important speech on promoting
cross-straits relations, and increase mutual understanding of
people on both sides of the straits and economic exchanges, and
make new contributions to the reunification and rejuvenation of
the motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
