<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0128 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 13:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran's Economy Expected to Grow by 5 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Iran's economy is expected to
grow by 5 percent during the current Iranian calendar year
ending on March 20, 1997, an official report said today.
</P>
<P>
The report by the Central Bank of Iran (CBI) announced that
the economic growth was registered at 4.5 percent during the
last Iranian calendar year.
</P>
<P>
The banking authorities said earlier that Iran is expected to
earn an oil export revenue of 19 billion U.S. dollars in the
current fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The revenue gained from oil and gas exports amounted to 14.5
billion dollars in the first three quarter of the current year,
the CBI report said.
</P>
<P>
The non-oil exports stood at 2.36 billion dollars in the
period, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
The total value of imports reached 11.63 billion dollars in
the past nine months. The trade surplus was 5.23 billion dollars
in the period.
</P>
<P>
The report said that all due debts were paid on schedule and
2.5 billion dollars were added to the foreign exchange reserves
of the country as a result of the surplus trade.
</P>
<P>
Continued economic stability has led to reducing the
inflation rate to less than 24 percent during the current
year. The average rate of inflation was 49.4 percent in the last
Iranian year, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
