<HEADLINE> Two Starve to Death in E. Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Two men starved to death in
eastern Uganda, a report reaching here said today.
</P>
<P>
Ananasio Onyago of Soni Parish, and Okoth Omuto of Mifuni
Parish, West Budama County, Eastern Tororo District, died in a
prolong famine, "the Monitor" reported.
</P>
<P>
And there were constant reports about collapsing.
</P>
<P>
Zebedayo Omoit, a local council chairman of Tororo District,
said a man collapsed at the official's home when he was asking
for help. The man was served a cup of tea later.
</P>
<P>
In eastern Pallisa District, headmaster of Kamonkoli Primary
School hardly escaped a lynch when he appealed the parents of his
pupils for money to feed the children with a porridge every
morning at 10:00.
</P>
<P>
The children were suffering from increasing case of collapsing
in recent two weeks. Earlier reports said the children in the
drought-hit area drinking water to reduce their hunger pain.
</P>
<P>
The worsening famine sparked exodus of rural population to
towns, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The residents in the drought-hit eastern area were selling
their assets at very low price for money. Patrick Okumi, a
resident of Eastern Kumi District, sold his bicycle at 35,000
Ugandan Shillings (some 35 U.S. Dollars) in Malera sub-county
market.
</P>
<P>
He said he can buy some 10 km of beans and some potatoes now
to support his family of eight some three weeks. He bought the
bicycle at 92,000 Ugandan Shillings (some 92 U.S. Dollars) last
November.
</P>
<P>
Present famine in Uganda was caused by long dry spells from
last December up to now. The eastern part suffers the most
critical food conditions. Earlier reports said 19 of 39 Ugandan
districts have been affected and some 2.1 million of residents
have been suffering from the famine.
</P>
<P>
Recent reports said famine looms in western Uganda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
