<HEADLINE> Suicide Thought Haunts HK Teenagers' Minds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 13 (Xinhua) -- One out of ten Hong Kong
teenagers thinks of suicide, with loneliness and depression as the
main causes, a recent study shows.
</P>
<P>
The thought occurs in 9.5 percent of primary school students
compared with 6.7 percent in secondary schools, according to a
survey conducted by the Center for Child Development at the Hong
Kong Baptist University.
</P>
<P>
Researchers found that suicidal youngsters could easily turn
inner anger and frustration into violence or drug abuse. They
suggested that children be taught to open up and share thoughts
with their peers.
</P>
<P>
The study covered 6,340 students at 15 Hong Kong primary and
secondary schools. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
