<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A fresh strike by Ugandan
Railways Corporation workers to Tororo, eastern Uganda has
paralysed cargo and passenger traffic to and from Nairobi, Kenya,
reported the local daily "the New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Over 500 passengers heading for Uganda were yesterday stranded
on Kenyan side of Malaba railway station, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The strikers abandoned the Tororo station yard on Monday
morning claiming they had not been paid their salary for January
and February plus arrears for December last year, January and
February this year.
</P>
<P>
The fresh strike followed an earlier one in January this year
by railway workers in Jinja, Kampala and Tororo main stations in
Uganda over similar claims.
</P>
<P>
The strikers were quoted by the paper as saying that the
corporation had pledged in January to pay their salary and
arrears at the end of every month but the contract was allegedly
breached prompting the fresh strike. 
</P>
