<HEADLINE> Macao to Launch "Afforestation Week" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Macao is to launch an
"Afforestation Week" from this coming weekend to improve local
citizens' awareness of the importance of planting and protecting
trees.
</P>
<P>
During the coming week, dozens of local community groups will
participate in various activities including lectures, exhibitions
and contests of potted plants. New books on the theme will be
published, and students will plant trees.
</P>
<P>
The event is held annually in the territory, whose land area
totals 21 square kilometers. Although it costs the government
515,000 patacas (about 65,000 US dollars) this year, officials say
 it is worthwhile since the green space in Macao is still small.
</P>
<P>
The acreage of afforested area in the Macao Peninsula, where 95
percent of the population live, grew from 230,000 square meters in
1988 to 450,000 square meters in 1996. Most of Macao's two islands
are covered by trees.  
</P>
</TEXT>
