<HEADLINE> 2 Killed, 11 Injured in Israeli-Jordanian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- At least two Israeli
school-girls were killed and 11 injured today near the
Israeli-Jordanian border when a Jordanian soldier opened fire at
the buses they were riding.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian border soldier, based in Naharayim in the
northern part of the border, opened fired with his automatic
rifle at one of the two buses carrying dozens of Israeli
students on school outing, Israeli Army Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The soldier managed to empty his ammunitions before being
overpowered by his fellow soldiers.
</P>
<P>
The casualty is expected to rise as some of the seriously
wounded have been taken to local Jordanian hospital for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
The place where the shooting took place is a scenic island
area in the Jordanian side of the Jordan River, which had been
occupied by Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israel returned this area to Jordan under the peace treaty
signed in 1994, but Israelis still have full access to the
favorite area for sightseeing and outing.
</P>
<P>
Today's shooting occurred during a time of rising tension
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian King Hussein and Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin
Netanyahu recently exchanged angry letters over the current
Israeli-Palestinian peace deadlock. King Hussein has strongly
criticized Israeli government for endangering the peace process
with its hardline policies. 
</P>
