<HEADLINE> Uganda's Coffee Exports Boosted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- With much coffee streaming in
from neighboring countries, coffee exports boosted rapidly in
Uganda, reported the local daily "the New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
Coffee experts were quoted as saying that Uganda could even
occupy the second spot on the world market with the continued
inflow from Zaire, Rwanda, Tanzania and Kenya.
</P>
<P>
"This does not mean Ugandans are not growing much coffee," a
source at uganda coffee development authority was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
Despite the influx, processors and exporters complained of a
declining quality in parts where foreign coffee is received or
processed, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The influx has been attributed to the favorable local prices
and the ease of access to the Ugandan market.
</P>
<P>
Kenyan coffee also found its way to Uganda through Mbale
bordering Kenya, while Tanzanian coffee have been streaming to
Masaka, about 80 km north of Tanzanian border. 
</P>
</TEXT>
