<HEADLINE> Tianjin Destroys Fake Commodities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Administration of Industry
and Commerce in Tianjin, a port city in north China, Wednesday
openly destroyed counterfeit products with a total market value of
2.4 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The destroyed goods included fake cigarettes, wine, foodstuff,
garments, video tapes and brand logo prints.
</P>
<P>
According to Shi Dong, director of the administration, the
destroyed items were but a small fraction of the fake and
counterfeit goods confiscated by his department.
</P>
<P>
In the recent two years, the administration dealt with more
than 3,000 cases and closed 300-odd underground sales or
production sites. "The market value of the confiscated goods
totalled around 400 million yuan," Shi said. 
</P>
