<HEADLINE> North, Northwest China Boost Foreign Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- North and Northwest China
demonstrated explosive growth in foreign trade last year.
</P>
<P>
The export volume of the two areas soared to 14.4 billion US
dollars last year, 11.7 percent up from 1995' figure.
</P>
<P>
Their import volume totalled 29.3 billion US dollars, 21
percent of the national total.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yixuan, a trade commissioner sent to Tianjin by the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC), said,
apart from the Beijing and Tianjin municipalities, these areas
remain under-developed though they have rich natural resources.
</P>
<P>
The export value of foreign-funded firms in Tianjin came to
2.15 billion US dollars, making half of the city's total export
last year. A local trade official predicted their export volume
would increase 25 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
Owing to changes in export structure, the export of high-tech
and value-added products increased rapidly while the export of raw
materials declined.
</P>
<P>
North and Northwest China cover one third of China's
territories and a population of 250 million.
</P>
<P>
The two areas have enhanced economic cooperation with the
Commonwealth of Independent States and other neighbouring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, a multi-ethnic area in
northwest China, has successfully held five trade fairs,
attracting 11,000 businessmen from 65 countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
