<HEADLINE> Rare Birds Discover Sanctuary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- More than 10,000 rare birds,
including cranes and swans, listed under state protection, have
come Shengjin Lake, a natural reserve in east China's Anhui
province, according to a recent survey.
</P>
<P>
The natural reserve has a total area of 13.3 hectares, and good
water uncontaminated by industrial wastes.
</P>
<P>
The rapidly increased number of rare birds in the lake area has
attracted attention both at home and abroad. Recently the Chinese
Ministry of Forestry and the World Wild Foundation have jointly
listed the lake as one of 40 natural reserves of international
importance in China. 
</P>
