<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Imposes Penalties On Illegal Video Parlors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
imposed heavy penalties under Emergency Regulations on illegal
video parlors and jackpot centers in and around Colombo.
</P>
<P>
According to official sources today, the regulations have
become necessary as these parlors and jackpot centers have been
enticing young school girls and boys as revealed in recent police
raids.
</P>
<P>
In certain areas it is reported that girls and boys are paid
heavy sums of money to participate in pornographic films.
</P>
<P>
Under the Emergency Regulations, the fine for those displaying
pornographic material in video parlors or those operating jackpot
centers will be fined Rs 100,000 (1,800 US dollars) or a
imprisonment term extending from 2 to 10 years.
</P>
<P>
The regulation also permits the confiscation and destruction of
equipment found on the premises.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, already 130 persons have been arrested
from 104 such places which violated these prohibitions. These
include 25 video parlors and 79 jackpot centers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
