<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Central China's Steel Plant to Issue Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Daye Special Steel Ltd Co, based
in Huangshi City in central China's Hubei Province, will issue 70
million A shares tomorrow for listing on the Shenzhen Securities
Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The issue, priced at 8.7 yuan for each share, is expected to
raise 595.7 million yuan, which will be used in a technological
renovation project and for the purchase of a gear-steel production
line.
</P>
<P>
The technological renovation project will focus on the
improvement of a refinery furnace and will involve a total
investment of 55.39 million yuan. It is expected to help upgrade
smelting quality and reduce energy consumption.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the gear-steel production line is under way in
Daye Steel Manufacturer and is to be completed later this
year. The line will be sold to Daye Special Steel at a price of
538.15 million yuan, with annual production capacity expected to
rise to 200,000 tons in three years' operation.
</P>
<P>
One of the nation's largest special steel manufacturers, Daye
now has an annual production capacity of 700,000 tons of special
steel and 550,000 tons of steel products. Its pre-tax profits
surpassed 130 million yuan last year and are expected to rise to
more than 168 million yuan this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
