<HEADLINE> First Polish Food Aid Arrives in Sofia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The first consignment of food aid
Poland is giving Bulgaria has arrived in Sofia, the Bulgarian
capital.
</P>
<P>
The Polish Press Agency said the 820 tons of wheat was sent to
Bulgaria by train, and is the part of the total 100,000 tons of
food aid Poland has offered Bulgaria, which is seriously short of
food.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria needs about 500,000 tons of grain between now and the
summer harvest season. There is only 90,000 tons of grain reserves
at present, says a report.
</P>
<P>
On February 27, Polish Prime Minister Wlodzimierz Cimoszewicz
made the offer to visiting Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov for
Poland to provide Bulgaria with 100,000 tons of grain to overcome
its shortage.
</P>
<P>
The report said about 55,000 tons of wheat would be sent to
Bulgaria by train, and the rest by ship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
