<HEADLINE> France Becomes Fourth Biggest Foreign Investor in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- France has become the
fourth biggest direct foreign investor in Brazil, the French
embassy in Brazil said.
</P>
<P>
France, who was the fifth in the foreign investor's list in
1995, unseated Britain last year.
</P>
<P>
The first three largest sources of foreign capital for Brazil
are the United States, Germany and Japan, according to Brazil's
central bank.
</P>
<P>
French investment totaled 900 million U.S. dollars by October
1996. French capital went mainly to the automobile industry,
services and the mining sector.
</P>
<P>
French investment in Brazil contracted in 1994 and rebounced
with the opening up of the Brazilian economy and President
Fernando Cardoso's visit to France in 1996, the French embassy
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
