<HEADLINE> Three Gorges Information Center To Be Built in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- An information center, which is
used to show the construction of the Three Gorges water control
project on the Yangtze River, is to be built in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Canadian firm Agra Monenco has signed a 1.5 million US dollars
worth of contract with China Yangtze Three Gorges Project
Development Corp (CTGPC), the project manager, to build the Three
Gorges Information Inquiry System.
</P>
<P>
The information center will exhibit the history, construction
progress and economic prospects of the project, today's "China
Daily" quoted Agra International Ltd Vice-President Henry Wang as
saying.
</P>
<P>
The center will help people at home and abroad better
understand the project, added Wang.
</P>
<P>
The contract followed a previous 11 million US dollars deal the
Canadian company signed with CTGPC last year to install a
computer-based management information system to run the future
Three Gorges power houses. 
</P>
