<HEADLINE> Drug Users Now 400,768 in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A total of 400,768
people take drugs in Colombia, and 80 percent of them are male in
the 18-44 age bracket, says the National Bureau of Narcotic
Substances.
</P>
<P>
The present number of drug users reflected a slight but
sustained increase since 1992.
</P>
<P>
Of the 117,058 people who tried drugs for the first time in the
past year, more than 89,000 smoked marijuana, about 11,000 used
basuco and 17,000 took cocaine, said the report.
</P>
<P>
About 87,500 of all first-time drug users were secondary school
males of 12-17 years.
</P>
<P>
The investigation showed that close to one million Colombians
have tried marijuana at least once, and more than 400,000 have
used it at some time in their lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
