<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Autonomy of National Minorities Areas Lauded (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhu) -- Deputies to the current session of
the Chinese legislature lauded China's system of regional autonomy
of national minorities, saying that without it there would not be
stability and prosperity in the areas populated by ethnic minority
groups.
</P>
<P>
Wang Chaowen, chairman of the Nationalities Committee of the
Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), which has been in its
fifth session since March 1, said: "The system of regional
autonomy of national minorities has played and will continue to
play a tremendous role in promoting national unity and social
stability, and regional autonomy of minority nationalities is a
key to the settlement of all issues concerning different ethnic
groups."
</P>
<P>
As an important political system of China, the system of
regional autonomy of national minorities demonstrates fully the
respect for and protection of the rights of national minorities.
</P>
<P>
Over past five decades, China has founded five autonomous
regions (Inner Mongolia, Ningxia, Tibetan, Xinjiang, and Guangxi),
30 autonomous prefectures and 124 autonomous counties.
</P>
<P>
A sample survey conducted last year showed that the population
of China's national minorities had reached 103 million. For
historical reasons, the overwhelming of them inhabit in the
outlying, mountainous areas.
</P>
<P>
The system of regional autonomy of minority nationalities
covers the political, economic, cultural and educational fields.
Official figures show that all the ethnic minorities in the
country have representation in the NPC and generally speaking, the
proportion of their deputies in all NPC deputies is much higher in
term of population.
</P>
<P>
Wang went on to say that a 1984 law and other regulations on
regional autonomy of national minorities have explicit terms to
specify that endeavors should be made to help the development of
the economic, cultural and educational undertakings in the areas
inhabited by people of various ethnic groups.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0262 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Regional Autonomy of National Minorities Areas Lauded (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The State also inclines to the autonomous areas in financial,
taxation, investment, loan-granting, foreign trade,
poverty-alleviation, educational and cultural policies, which has
helped to promote development in the ethnic-minority areas.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the per capita income of farmers in the
autonomous areas reached 1,142 yuan in 1995, higher than the
national average for farmers. The average economic growth rate in
the five autonomous regions also exceeded the national average
last year.
</P>
<P>
Wang noted that the system of regional autonomy of minority
nationalities is very instrumental to the fostering of cadres of
minority nationalities.
</P>
<P>
"As for myself, I would not be what I'm like today, if without
the system," said Wang, who had been a cowherd of the Miao ethnic
group till 11, became China's youngest official at the ministry
level when he was 46.
</P>
<P>
Official figures show that the number of carders of minority
nationalities in China has exceeded 2.48 million.
</P>
<P>
In China, the heads of autonomous areas at all levels are
assumed by people of ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
To cater to the latest developments, China will modify the 1984
law and those formulated earlier in the near future, according to
Wang.
</P>
<P>
"Stepping up legislation will provide an effective guarantee
for the system of regional autonomy of national minorities," he
said.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that the Nationalities Committee will
promulgate a law concerning protection of the rights and interests
of people of the national minorities scattered around, a law on
the language and characters of the ethnic groups and regulations
on autonomy in the five autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Wang expressed his confidence that a relatively
complete system of socialist legality and supervision for issues
relating to national minorities will be set up before the year
2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
