<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stability, Development Feature China's March toward New Century (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Despite a bunch of thorny
problems, China is expected to maintain its momentum in political
stability, economic development, and social progress through the
next century.
</P>
<P>
This is the conclusion drawn in the current session of the
National People's Congress (NPC), China's legislature, which has
been in session since the first date of this month.
</P>
<P>
Since the early 1990s, China has made great strides in reform
and opening-up and its modernization has entered a new period,
said an NPC deputy. The economic restructuring aimed at
establishing a socialist market economy is penetrating and the
country has scored marked progress in national economic and social
development. Its social productive forces, comprehensive national
strength and people's living standards have ascended a new height.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the campaign to build a clean and honest government
and exercise an all-round administration over social security
issues have been effectively strengthened. And harsh punishment
has been meted out to corruption and crimes.
</P>
<P>
As a developing country, China has won increasing respects
from the international community for its principle of fairness,
essential flexibility and posture of neither being haughty nor
humble on the world arena.
</P>
<P>
NPC deputies gave a full affirmation to these encouraging
achievements. Prof. Zhang Zhongli, president of the Shanghai
Academy of Social Sciences, said tremendous achievements in
China's domestic and diplomatic fields over recent years have been
scored during the period of smooth transition from the second to
third generation of collective leadership. The Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core have handled positively and
appropriately a number of major domestic and international complex
problems under the guidance of Deng Xiaoping's theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and demonstrated their
capabilities of coping with the overall situation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Deputies from China's military circle also consented to Zhang's
views.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of Central Military Commission,
and other army generals held that the third generation of
collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at its core is a staunch
and mature leading body, which, they stressed, is worth trust and
support of the whole party, the whole army and all ethnic groups
in China.
</P>
<P>
The capability of the new generation of leadership to deal with
complex issues has withstood tests and been proven convincingly in
the three years' arduous efforts to bring inflation under control.
</P>
<P>
Though there is no precedent to go by in the country's endeavor
to establish a socialist market economy, the Chinese leaders came
out with an effective, complicated prescription which was focused
on readjusting the monetary and financial policies, supplemented
with administrative and legal means.
</P>
<P>
The move has scaled down inflation rate from the 21.7 percent
in 1994 to 6.1 percent in 1996 while maintaining an economic
growth rate of around 10 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0269 </DOCNO>
