<HEADLINE> China's Exhibition a Success at Berlin Tourism Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- China's exhibition at the
five-day Berlin International Tourism Fair has been a great
success.
</P>
<P>
More than 100,000 visitors, including 53,000 professionals,
attended the fair.
</P>
<P>
The 77 members of the Chinese delegation were from the National
Tourism Bureau, seven provincial tourism bureaus, 15 travel
agencies and two airlines.
</P>
<P>
China's exhibition, focussed on the Visit China '97 tourism
campaign, attracted some 400 trade visitors every day.
</P>
<P>
Berlin International Tourism Fair is the largest of its kind in
the world. German Chancellor Helmut Kohl attended the opening
ceremony last Saturday. 
