<HEADLINE> Era of Israeli-Russian Hostility Is Over: Netanyahu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu said the relations between Israel and Russia
has reached a new level and the era of hostility is over.
</P>
<P>
"Russia and Israel have reached a new level of relations in
politics and economy," Netanyahu told a news conference before
ending his visit in Moscow. "They will be able to strengthen
friendship and mutual understanding."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that his visit will further promote bilateral
relations, especially in the economic field.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli prime minister said that during his stay, he had a
general discussion with Russian leaders on the issue of Russia
supplying natural gas to Israel.
</P>
<P>
He also confirmed that the two sides are interested in jointly
re-equipping Russian military aircraft and selling them to third
countries.
</P>
<P>
On the Middle East issue, Netanyahu praised Russia's active
role and hoped that Russia could help bring Syria back to the
negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
However, he acknowledged that Israel has had differences with
Russia and the United States over the issue of building new
Israeli settlements in east Jerusalem. Russian President Boris
Yeltsin expressed concern over the issue during his talks with
Netanyahu on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
As to Russia's nuclear cooperation with Iran, Yeltsin said his
country did not and will not sell missile weapons to that country.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu, who arrived on Monday for his a three-day official
visit, has held talks with President Yeltsin, Prime Minister
Viktor Chernomyrdin and Foreign Minister Yevgeny Primakov. 
</P>
</TEXT>
