<HEADLINE> Agassi To Play Davis Cup for United States </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Andre Agassi will play singles
for the United States in a Davis Cup World Group quarter-final tie
against the Netherlands next month, captain Tom Gullikson said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gullikson confirmed the news that Agassi leaked on Tuesday
after he lost his first-round match at the 2.3 million-dollar
Champions Cup tournament in Indian Wells.
</P>
<P>
It was Agassi's fourth match loss in a row, but Gullikson said
he thought Agassi's game had improved enough recently to warrant
his inclusion.
</P>
<P>
Gullikson had already named Jim Courier for the tie, which will
be played at Newport Beach, California, April 4-6. Courier was
instrumental in the United States' first-round victory over Brazil.
</P>
<P>
Gullikson selected the world number-two doubles team of Rick
Leach and Jonathan Stark to play doubles. 
</P>
