<HEADLINE> PML(N) Sweeps Senate Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistan Muslim League (N)
led by Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif today won a glorious victory in
the Senate elections held in all the four provinces.
</P>
<P>
Unofficial results showed that out of a total of 46 Senate
seats the PML (N) secured 23, the Awami (People's) National Party
(ANP) four, the Pakistan People's Party (PPP) three and the
Mohajir Qaumi Movement (MQM) three.
</P>
<P>
PML(N) secured ten seats in Punjab, five in North West Frontier
Province (NWFP), three in Sindh and Balochistan each and two in
the Federal Capital while its arch rival PPP got only three seats
in Sindh.
</P>
<P>
Elections for a total of 27 Senate seats were held in Sindh,
NWFP and Balochistan today while all 15 senators from Punjab and
the Federal Capital had been elected unopposed. Election for the
four seats from the Federal-Administered Tribal Areas had been
postponed.
</P>
<P>
Elections of almost half of the Senate seats are held every
third year. Last time the elections for Senate seats were held on
March 2, 1994.
</P>
<P>
The PML(N) now holds 41 seats in the 87-seat Senate while its
arch rival, the PPP, has only 19 seats. With the support of its
allies, the PML(N) is sure to have a two-thirds majority in the
Senate.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
