<HEADLINE> Italian Government, Unions Reach Job Accord </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Italian government and union
representatives reached agreement today on a plan to introduce job
flexibility in the public sector, sources close to the unions said.
</P>
<P>
Under the plan, the public sector will introduce mobility
incentives, long-term training programs, greater use of part-time
work, home work and formal trainee contracts at reduced pay.
</P>
<P>
Today's agreement will become part of the Pact for Jobs, the
job creation program underwritten by unions, management and
government. 
</P>
