<HEADLINE> Romania, Hungary Tighten Political, Economical Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Romania and Hungary signed five
agreements today to boost their political and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed after the visiting Romanian Prime
Minister Victor Ciorbea held talks with his Hungarian counterpart
Horn Gyula on a wide range of topics including bilateral relations
and ethnic minority issues.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian premier told a press conference after the talks
that the cooperation and strategic partnership between Romania and
Hungary as well as the way they absorb ethnic minorities into
government could serve as an example for other countries in the
region.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea, who arrived here today on a two-day official visit,
said that strengthening political, economic and military
cooperation in an all-round way is of great significance to both
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Hungarian premier acknowledged that the development of
bilateral relations has been encouraging since the new Romanian
government came to office in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea is the first Romanian prime minister to visit Hungary
in many years, and Hungary is also the first country he has
visited in his capacity as prime minister. 
</P>
</TEXT>
