<HEADLINE> Chanteur Wins Fourth Stage in Paris-Nice Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Pascal Chanteur showed
his class by winning the fourth stage of the Paris-Nice race on
Wednesday, while compatriot Laurent Jalabert maintained his grip
on the leader's white jersey.
</P>
<P>
Chanteur, 29, led home a group of seven riders to capture the
165-kilometer stage from Montlucon to Clermont-Ferrand, the third
stage victory of his career.
</P>
<P>
ONCE rider Jalabert, looking for his third successive
Paris-Nice title, finished third behind Chanteur and Swiss rider
Laurent Dufaux in the leading group.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert came under attack at several points during a
hard-fought race, notably from the Festina team, but withstood the
pressure and then prompted the decisive breakaway 22km from the
finish.
</P>
<P>
The main pack, led by Italian Fabio Baldato, finished 14
seconds adrift after a vigorous pursuit in the closing stages.
</P>
</TEXT>
