<BODY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed, Two Injured in Karachi Bomb Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 12 (Xinhua) -- At least one person was killed,
two others injured in a blast occurred earlier today in Karachi,
Pakistan's biggest city, sources said.
</P>
<P>
The blast was caused by a foreign-made hand grenade thrown at a
music shop in a crowded market located at the southern part of the
port city, the sources quoted bomb disposal experts as saying.
</P>
<P>
A 40-year-old shop salesman was killed in the blast and two
others including a teenager were injured, they said.
</P>
<P>
No people or group has claimed responsibility for the blast so
far.
</P>
<P>
Two bomb blasts rocked Karachi early last week, one damaging
the office of a local Urdu language newspaper, but they caused
only minor casualties.  
</P>
</TEXT>
