<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sampras Suffers Defeat in Champions Cup Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Pete Sampras suffered his
first defeat in 20 matches when he lost to Bohdan Ulihrach of
Czech Republic in straight sets at the Champions Cup tennis
tournament in Indian Wells on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ulihrach, ranked 43rd in the world, defeated the world number
one 7-6 (7/5), 7-5 to advance to the third round of the 2.3
million-U.S. dollar tournament.
</P>
<P>
Ulihrach claimed his second career victory over Sampras, whose
last defeat was to Germany's Boris Becker in the round-robin phase
of the 1996 ATP Tour World Championship.
</P>
<P>
Sampras went on to beat Becker in the final of that event.
Coming into Wednesday's match, Sampras had dropped just three sets
since the semi-finals of the Australian Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
