<HEADLINE> Chinese Women's Delegation Visits Ireland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women's delegation
concluded a six-day visit to Ireland today, promoting mutual
understanding between Chinese and Irish women.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the delegation, headed by secretary Tian
Shulan of the Secretariat of the All-China Women's Federation,
inspected Irish social welfare projects and exchanged views with
Irish women representatives on issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
On March 8, the International Women's Day, Irish Deputy Prime
Minister and Foreign Minister Dick Spring met with the Chinese
delegation.
</P>
<P>
Spring said that the Irish government would strive to
strengthen contacts between Irish and Chinese women in an effort
to enhance mutual understanding. 
