<HEADLINE> Orange Claims Market Leadership in Mobile Phone Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Mobile telephone company Orange,
49 percent owned by Hutchison Whampoa of Hongkong, is now claiming
leadership of the rapidly growing UK market, according to a press
release by the Invest in Britain Bureau.
</P>
<P>
It is also well established in France and Germany and plans
further European expansion soon.
</P>
<P>
With more than 30,000 new subscribers a month, the company had
850,000 customers at the end of February in Britain alone.
</P>
<P>
In Europe as a whole it ended 1996 with 1.358 million
customers. Orange's turnover last year rose by over 170 percent to
well over 920 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The press release quoted Hans Snook, the managing director of
Orange, said:"All the information we have from statisticians,
dealers and distributors says that we are undoubtedly the fastest
growing network this year."
</P>
<P>
The company, based in Darlington, North East England, was
formed in 1994. It was floated on the stock market last year when
the Hongkong share was reduced to under 50 percent from 68
percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
