<DOCNO> XIE19970313.0318 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Works Out 1997 Work Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government today
submitted its 1997 work plan to the parliament, listing the
economic and financial stability and the restoration of
production among top targets.
</P>
<P>
The government will strictly control finance and currency,
effectively curb inflation and raise actual wages so as to
realize the stability and harmonization of the whole society,
Minister for Planning Emanuel Carneiro said.
</P>
<P>
The government, with a total of 890 million U.S. Dollars of
foreign exchange controllable, will spend 340 million dollars to
meet administration expenditures and the rest on various economic
activities, he said.
</P>
<P>
1997 is the first year for the war-torn southern African
country to implement the integrated plan on the restoration and
development of its national economy, he said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the success of the work plan depends on the
strengthened power and credit of the government, the
consolidation of peace process, the reduction of foreign debts
and so on, said Carneiro.
</P>
<P>
The development in the private sector, primary education and
professional training will be conducive to the carrying-out of
the work plan, he added. enditem

