<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S. Africa, S. America to Hold Joint Navy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The navies of South Africa,
Argentina, Brazil and Uruguay will hold joint exercises in South
African waters later this month, the South African navy said in a
statement today.
</P>
<P>
The three South American states will send six ships, including
guided-missile frigates, corvettes and a tanker, to take part in
the exercise together with South Africa's nine ships and a
submarine, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The exercise is aimed at improving cooperation and extending
understanding between the navies of these countries, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The visiting ships will rendezvous with a South African task
team on March 15 and arrive in Simon's Town, near Cape Town, two
days later.
</P>
<P>
The visiting warships will also attend the South African
navy's 75th anniversary celebrations and take part in an
international fleet review on April 5, the statement said.
enditem

